            <title>[LU-14166] sanity test_27o: able to create /mnt/lustre/d27o.sanity/f27o.sanity</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14166</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Olaf Faaland &amp;lt;faaland1@llnl.gov&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/99eb1259-ea98-4fee-b422-0dd2e6f538f5&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/99eb1259-ea98-4fee-b422-0dd2e6f538f5&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test_27o failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;able to create /mnt/lustre/d27o.sanity/f27o.sanity
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The test sets fail_loc to OBD_FAIL_OST_ENOSPC on all OSTs to force preallocations to fail, then creates new files to consume already-allocated objects.  It then attempts to create a new file, which should fail with ENOSPC.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Test log lines preceeding the error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;osp.lustre-OST0007-osc-MDT0003.prealloc_last_id=33
osp.lustre-OST0007-osc-MDT0003.prealloc_last_seq=0x4c0000401
osp.lustre-OST0007-osc-MDT0003.prealloc_next_id=4
osp.lustre-OST0007-osc-MDT0003.prealloc_next_seq=0x4c0000401
osp.lustre-OST0007-osc-MDT0003.prealloc_reserved=0
osp.lustre-OST0007-osc-MDT0003.prealloc_status=-28
CMD: trevis-68vm7 lctl set_param fail_loc=0x215
fail_loc=0x215
CMD: trevis-68vm8 lctl get_param -n lo[vd].*.qos_maxage
 sanity test_27o: @@@@@@ FAIL: able to create /mnt/lustre/d27o.sanity/f27o.sanity 
  Trace dump:
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh:5907:error()
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/sanity.sh:1749:test_27o()
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh:6210:run_one()
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh:6259:run_one_logged()
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh:6099:run_test()
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/sanity.sh:1754:main()
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;







